OL,7,FHe told ITV Border: "The big
OL,8,Fdifference is that a full size diesel
OL,9,Fengine uses big hammers, whereas the
OL,10,Fengines (on model railways) uses tiny
OL,11,Ftweezers."
OL,13,FHe says: "It takes immense amounts of
OL,14,Fpatience painting the little figures,
OL,15,Fwhich are only six millimetres high is
OL,16,Fa laborious job that needs a
OL,17,Fmagnifying glass and a lamp."
